```sh
find ./aio/ -type d -exec imagemin {}/* --out-dir={} \;
find ./aio/ -type d -exec imagemin {}/* --out-dir={} --plugin=mozjpeg \;
find ./aio/ -type d -exec imagemin {}/* --out-dir={} --plugin.pngquant.quality={0.1,0.2} \;
```

Different from previous optimization passes, this change:
* Uses lossy compression. I looked over most of the changes, only only saw one image where the output was noticeably _slightly_ lower quality.
* Optimizes jpeg, gif, and svg assets

